WEBVTT

00:03.670 --> 00:07.716
[Flamenco-Style Guitar Intro]

00:10.969 --> 00:15.140
[Pop, Up-Tempo]

00:17.000 --> 00:23.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:30.280 --> 00:32.741
Our glorious city

00:35.076 --> 00:38.079
Was built by the divinities

00:38.204 --> 00:42.792
By gods who saw fit

00:42.876 --> 00:45.378
To bestow

00:49.507 --> 00:52.761
The gift of a paradise

00:54.596 --> 00:59.267
Peaceful and harmonious upon

00:59.392 --> 01:03.563
Us mere mortals below

01:06.441 --> 01:08.943
And made El Dorado

01:09.027 --> 01:14.115
The magnificent and golden

01:14.240 --> 01:17.869
One thousand years ago

01:18.995 --> 01:23.833
El Dorado
El Dorado

01:23.917 --> 01:32.133
El Dora-a-a-a-do

01:41.434 --> 01:43.812
-Today, we sail...
-[Nickers]

01:43.895 --> 01:45.981
to conquer the New World...

01:46.106 --> 01:50.986
-for Spain, for glory, for gold!
-[Crowd Clamoring]

01:51.069 --> 01:55.031
-[Crowd Cheering]
-[Man Shouting] Viva Cortes!

01:55.156 --> 01:57.200
[Whinnying]

01:57.325 --> 02:00.912
[Grunts]
Altivo, eyes forward.

02:04.541 --> 02:06.710
-Seven!
-All right!

02:06.793 --> 02:09.670
-Yes!
-Partner! Hee-hee!

02:09.795 --> 02:11.673
-Tons of gold for you
-Hey!

02:11.798 --> 02:13.675
-Tons of gold for me
-Hey!

02:13.800 --> 02:16.303
-[Both] Tons of gold for we
-Hey!

02:16.428 --> 02:18.763
-One more roll!
-[Plucks Notes]

02:18.847 --> 02:21.349
Uh, guys, you're broke!

02:21.474 --> 02:25.020
-You got nothin' to bet with!
-Oh, yeah? I got this!

02:25.103 --> 02:27.772
-[Man]A map!
-A map?
-A map!

02:27.897 --> 02:31.109
A map of the wonders
of the New World.

02:31.234 --> 02:34.487
-Wow! Let's have a look.
-[Scoffs]

02:34.571 --> 02:37.365
[Indistinct Muttering]

02:37.449 --> 02:39.951
Uh, Tulio!

02:40.076 --> 02:43.872
-Excuse us, for one moment, please.
-Tulio, look!

02:43.997 --> 02:46.666
-El Dorado, the city of gold.
-[Sighs]

02:46.791 --> 02:49.669
This could be our destiny, our fate.

02:49.794 --> 02:51.671
Miguel, if I believed in fate,

02:51.796 --> 02:53.882
I wouldn't be playing
with loaded dice.

02:54.007 --> 02:56.927
-Hmmm. [Chuckling]
-Not with the face. No, no, no, no, no.

02:57.010 --> 02:59.846
-No! No! No!
-[Whimpering, Panting]

02:59.888 --> 03:02.265
I said one more roll!

03:02.349 --> 03:04.809
My map against your cash.

03:04.893 --> 03:07.020
-Hmm?
-[Dice Clattering]

03:07.145 --> 03:10.690
-All right, peewee. You're on!
-Not with those!

03:10.815 --> 03:15.403
This time we use my dice.
Ehh, got a problem with that?

03:15.528 --> 03:18.073
[Whimpers] No.

03:18.198 --> 03:20.992
[Whispers]
I'm going to kill you.

03:23.578 --> 03:27.249
Come on, baby.
Papa needs that crappy map.

03:27.374 --> 03:29.960
[Giggles]

03:31.127 --> 03:33.755
-[Scoffs]
-[Blows]

03:33.880 --> 03:36.007
Stop that!

03:36.091 --> 03:39.427
Show me seven!

03:44.140 --> 03:46.935
[Gasps]

03:47.018 --> 03:49.145
[Crowd Exclaims, Cheers]

03:49.229 --> 03:51.606
-Seven!
-All right!

03:51.690 --> 03:53.692
-Seven!
-[Groans]

03:53.817 --> 03:57.612
[Laughing] There it is!
Well, nice doing business with you.

03:59.072 --> 04:03.952
-[Grunting] I knew it!
-[Crowd Gasping]

04:04.077 --> 04:05.787
[Gasps]

04:05.871 --> 04:08.456
Your dice are loaded!

04:09.666 --> 04:12.294
What?
You gave me loaded dice?

04:12.419 --> 04:14.796
[Grunts]

04:16.214 --> 04:19.634
-He gave me loaded dice!
-[Crowd Murmurs]

04:19.759 --> 04:24.681
-Guard, arrest him!
-You dare to impugn my honor?

04:24.806 --> 04:26.808
He was the one who was cheating!

04:26.933 --> 04:29.895
Arrest him! He tricked these sailors
and took their money!

04:30.020 --> 04:32.189
-Oh, now, I'm the thief?
-Yes.

04:32.272 --> 04:34.274
Take a look in the mirror, pal!

04:34.357 --> 04:37.152
Oh, you better give them
that money back, or I'll--

04:37.277 --> 04:39.696
-En garde!
-En garde, yourself.

04:39.821 --> 04:43.450
I will give you the honor
of a quick and painless death.

04:43.575 --> 04:46.661
But not with that. Ha!
I prefer to fight fairly. Aha!

04:46.745 --> 04:50.248
-[Growls]
-Well, any last words?

04:50.332 --> 04:52.501
I will cut you to ribbons,

04:52.626 --> 04:54.586
-fool!
-Such mediocrity.

04:54.711 --> 04:56.588
Let your sword do the talking.

04:56.713 --> 05:01.259
-I will.
It will be loquacious to a fault!
-Ha! Take that!

05:01.384 --> 05:04.930
[Both Grunting]

05:05.013 --> 05:09.768
-You... mincing, fencing, twit.
-Ah, you fight like my sister.

05:09.851 --> 05:12.562
I fought your sister.
That's a compliment.

05:12.687 --> 05:14.773
-Braggart!
-Heathen!

05:14.898 --> 05:17.317
-[Man] Kill him!
-Not the face. Not the face.

05:18.735 --> 05:21.863
[All Gasping, Clamoring]

05:21.947 --> 05:24.491
Ladies and gentlemen,
we've decided it's a draw.

05:24.616 --> 05:26.076
[Miguel]
Thank you all for coming.

05:26.159 --> 05:28.912
-You've been great. See you soon.
-Adios!

05:30.789 --> 05:33.792
-Congratulations. You're very good.
-No. That was good.

05:33.875 --> 05:36.002
-Very--
-[Snort]

05:36.086 --> 05:38.880
-[Gasping]
-[Mooing, Snorting]

05:39.005 --> 05:41.883
-We should have kept
our swords, I think.
-Y-Yeah.

05:42.008 --> 05:44.010
-[Snorting]
-[Tulio Whispering]
Yeah, I've got a plan.

05:44.136 --> 05:47.556
-What is it?
-Uh, well-Uh, you...

05:47.681 --> 05:50.851
-pet him, and... I'll...
-Yeah.

05:50.934 --> 05:53.603
run!

05:53.728 --> 05:56.815
-Uh, well, thanks a lot!
-[Bull Bellowing]

06:00.152 --> 06:02.154
[Both] Whoa!

06:05.407 --> 06:08.493
-There they are!
-[Hooves Screeching]

06:08.618 --> 06:12.664
[Male Chorus]Hey, hey, hey, hey
Hey, hey, hey, hey

06:16.376 --> 06:19.087
-[Woman Screaming]
-Bye. Thank you!

06:19.171 --> 06:21.047
-[All Gasping]
-[Bellowing]

06:21.173 --> 06:22.549
[Chorus] Olé

06:22.674 --> 06:24.551
[Groans]

06:25.927 --> 06:28.096
[Fabric Ripping]

06:28.221 --> 06:30.724
[Both Grunting]

06:30.807 --> 06:33.477
-Uhh--
-Ohh--

06:34.978 --> 06:36.938
-I'll bet we can make that.
-[Men Shouting]

06:37.063 --> 06:39.733
-[Guard] There they are!
-Two pesetas says we can't.

06:39.816 --> 06:41.735
You're on!

06:41.818 --> 06:45.155
[Both Yelling]

06:45.238 --> 06:47.783
-[Miguel] You lose!
-[Coins Jingling]

06:49.868 --> 06:52.037
-[Miguel]Ohhh!
-[Tulio] Whoa! What's happening here?

06:52.162 --> 06:55.332
We're both in barrels.
That's the extent of my knowledge.

06:58.543 --> 07:00.670
[Muffled Grunts, Groans]

07:06.259 --> 07:08.136
Okay, Miguel,
we gotta move fast.

07:08.261 --> 07:11.515
-On three, we jump out
and head for the dock.
-Good. Good. Excellent.

07:11.598 --> 07:14.601
[Together]
One, two, three--

07:14.684 --> 07:17.145
-[Both Grunting] Th-Three!
-[Creaking]

07:17.229 --> 07:20.273
-[Both Straining] Three! Ohh!
-[Creaking Continues]

07:20.398 --> 07:22.734
[Straining]
Three!

07:29.241 --> 07:33.620
[Tulio]Uh, you ready?
Ah, okay. One more. Let's go.

07:33.745 --> 07:38.458
[Together]
One, two, three!

07:38.542 --> 07:41.461
-[Fly Buzzing]
-[Wind Whistling]

07:41.586 --> 07:44.089
-Excuse us.
-Okay. We're outta here.

07:44.172 --> 07:47.592
-Who ordered the, uh, pickles?
-[Sailor Laughing]

07:50.178 --> 07:52.556
[Grunting]

07:52.639 --> 07:54.558
Cortes!

07:54.683 --> 08:00.522
-My crew was as carefully chosen
as the disciples of Christ.
-[Cracks Knuckles]

08:00.647 --> 08:04.818
-And I will not tolerate stowaways.
-[Gulps]

08:04.901 --> 08:09.030
You will be flogged.
And when we put into Cuba to resupply,

08:09.156 --> 08:12.367
God willing, you will
be flogged some more...

08:12.451 --> 08:14.953
and then enslaved
on the sugar plantations...

08:15.036 --> 08:17.205
for the rest of your miserable lives.

08:17.289 --> 08:19.666
To the brig.

08:19.791 --> 08:22.794
All right!
Cuba!

08:22.919 --> 08:25.130
-[Gasps]
-[Gasps]

08:30.802 --> 08:34.472
[Whistling]

08:34.597 --> 08:36.515
-[Chuckles]
-[Nickers]

08:36.640 --> 08:39.311
Hey, Altivo!
Ah-ta-ta, not for you!

08:39.436 --> 08:42.272
You're on half rations.
Orders from Cortes.

08:43.357 --> 08:46.276
-[Gasps]
-[Banging]

08:46.360 --> 08:50.906
[Banging Continues]

08:53.575 --> 08:56.912
So, uh, how's the--
How's the escape plan coming?

08:58.914 --> 09:01.416
All right.
All right. Wait!

09:01.541 --> 09:03.752
-I'm getting something.
-Yeah.

09:08.548 --> 09:11.426
Okay!
Here's the plan.

09:11.510 --> 09:14.221
-In the dead of night,
you and I grab some provisions,
-Mm-hm.

09:14.346 --> 09:16.765
hijack one of those long boats,

09:16.848 --> 09:21.770
and then we row back to Spain
like there's no mañana!

09:21.853 --> 09:24.356
-Back to Spain, yeah?
-Yeah.

09:24.481 --> 09:26.525
-In a rowboat.
-You got it!

09:26.608 --> 09:29.569
Great. Sensational.
And that-that's your plan, is it?

09:29.653 --> 09:32.781
-That's pretty much it.
-Well, I like it.

09:32.864 --> 09:36.034
-So, how do we get on deck?
-Umm.

09:36.118 --> 09:39.621
In the dead of night,
you and I grab some provisions,

09:39.705 --> 09:43.125
-hijack one of those longboats--
-Uh, great.

09:43.208 --> 09:45.210
Okay, what's your idea, smart guy?

09:45.293 --> 09:47.796
Wh-Wh-What do you mean? Don't ask
me that! You're the one with the plans.

09:47.921 --> 09:51.258
-[Horse Whinnying]
- Wait, I-I have an idea.

09:51.341 --> 09:53.969
Uh, come on. Give me--
Give me a boost.

09:54.094 --> 09:56.847
Hey, Altivo.

09:56.930 --> 09:59.307
Altivo.

09:59.391 --> 10:01.768
You want a nice apple?
Come and get it.

10:01.893 --> 10:05.480
-[Hooves Clattering]
-You have to do a trick for me first.

10:05.605 --> 10:07.607
Huh?
[Sputtering]

10:07.649 --> 10:10.068
All you have to do
is find a pry bar.

10:10.193 --> 10:15.324
A long piece of iron
with a hooky thing at the end. Yeah?

10:15.449 --> 10:18.827
-Miguel, you're talking to a horse!
-[Hooves Clattering]

10:18.910 --> 10:21.705
That's it, Altivo,
find the pry bar.

10:21.788 --> 10:24.499
-Yes, find the prybar.
-[Whinnying]

10:24.624 --> 10:27.711
-He can't understand "pry bar."
-[Clattering Continues]

10:27.794 --> 10:31.131
He's a dumb horse.
There's no way--

10:31.214 --> 10:33.592
[Whinnying]

10:34.926 --> 10:38.930
Well, it's not a pry bar.

10:39.014 --> 10:41.808
-[Wind Howling]
-[Ship Creaking]

10:49.983 --> 10:54.154
-[Gasps]
-[Nickers]

10:54.279 --> 10:58.325
Oh, Altivo.
Oh, thank you, old boy.

10:58.408 --> 11:02.162
Listen, if we can
ever return the favor--

11:02.287 --> 11:06.208
For Pete's sake, Miguel,
he's a ruthless warhorse, not a poodle.

11:06.249 --> 11:08.168
Come on,
before he licks you to death.

11:08.251 --> 11:11.797
-Adios.
-[Whinnies]

11:13.590 --> 11:16.551
Shh, shh. Shh.
Quiet, please.

11:16.677 --> 11:19.012
-What's the matter with him?
-Oh, he wants his apple.

11:19.096 --> 11:22.307
-Well, give it to him
before he wakes the whole ship!
-[Bellowing]

11:22.432 --> 11:25.269
-Fetch!
-[Whinnying] Huh?

11:27.271 --> 11:29.856
[Snoring]

11:32.442 --> 11:34.528
[Gasps]
Hmm?

11:34.653 --> 11:36.905
[Hoof beats Clatter, Stop Abruptly]

11:36.989 --> 11:38.949
-Huh?
-Huh?
-[Whinnying]

11:40.033 --> 11:43.412
[Whinnying]

11:43.537 --> 11:46.748
-Altivo!
-Huh? Miguel!

11:46.873 --> 11:49.084
[Yelling]

11:49.209 --> 11:51.420
-Altivo, I'm coming!
-Miguel!

11:51.545 --> 11:54.006
Just hang on!
I'm right here, old boy!

11:54.089 --> 11:56.633
-Have you lost your mind?
-Help is coming!

11:56.717 --> 11:59.094
[Gasps]

11:59.219 --> 12:01.096
Ho-o-ly ship!

12:01.221 --> 12:04.016
[Miguel, Tulio] Whoa!

12:04.141 --> 12:08.687
[All Gasping]

12:10.272 --> 12:13.734
-Loop the rope under the horse!
-Yes!

12:19.865 --> 12:22.784
On the count of three,
pull back on the rope.

12:22.868 --> 12:24.828
-What? [Gasps]
-Three!

12:25.913 --> 12:27.831
-[Tulio] Pull!
-[Grunting]

12:34.504 --> 12:37.549
Tulio!
Hey, it worked!

12:41.803 --> 12:44.556
Did any of the supplies make it?

12:44.681 --> 12:47.476
-Well, uh, yes and no.
-[Crunching Sound]

12:50.020 --> 12:53.398
Ohhh, great!

12:53.482 --> 12:56.485
Look on the positive side.
At least things can't get--

12:57.694 --> 13:00.489
Excuse me.
Were you going to say "worse"?

13:00.572 --> 13:02.491
-No. No.
-No? You're sure?

13:02.574 --> 13:04.701
-Absolutely not.
I've revised the whole thing.
-Okay, because--

13:04.826 --> 13:07.913
-[Tulio] Yeah,
we're at least in a rowboat.
-We're in a rowboat, exactly.

13:08.038 --> 13:09.957
[Miguel]
You miss nothing.

13:11.083 --> 13:15.045
[Grunting, Groaning]

13:15.128 --> 13:19.633
-[Grunting, Groaning Continue]
-[Whinnying]

13:21.843 --> 13:23.762
[Yelling]

13:30.102 --> 13:32.187
-[Groaning]
-[Gasps]

13:32.271 --> 13:34.398
[Together] Ahh!

13:36.108 --> 13:38.986
[Coughs]

13:42.072 --> 13:44.950
[Smacking Lips]

13:48.370 --> 13:50.581
[All Sobbing]

14:03.302 --> 14:08.432
Tulio, did you ever imagine
it would end like this?

14:08.515 --> 14:11.852
-The horse is a surprise.
-[Nickers]

14:11.935 --> 14:16.190
Any... regrets?

14:16.315 --> 14:19.818
Besides dying?
Yeah.

14:19.943 --> 14:25.199
I never... had enough... gold.

14:26.450 --> 14:32.080
My regret, besides dying, is...

14:32.206 --> 14:35.667
our greatest adventure
is over before it began,

14:35.792 --> 14:38.795
and no one will even remember us.

14:38.879 --> 14:43.008
Well, if it's
any consolation, Miguel,

14:43.091 --> 14:46.637
you... made my life...

14:46.720 --> 14:48.722
an adventure.
[Sobbing]

14:48.806 --> 14:52.267
And if it's any consolation,
Tulio, [Sniffles]

14:52.351 --> 14:56.355
-you made my life... rich.
-[Sobbing Continues]

14:56.480 --> 14:59.733
[Scoffs, Sputters]

14:59.817 --> 15:03.987
[Both Sobbing]

15:04.112 --> 15:06.031
[Shuddering Gasp]

15:08.283 --> 15:10.786
[Moans]

15:15.541 --> 15:17.709
-[Gasps] Is it?
-Hmm. [Gasps]

15:17.835 --> 15:19.962
It is! It's-It's--
It's-It's-It's--

15:20.087 --> 15:22.214
[Both] It's land!

15:28.220 --> 15:30.931
-[Both Screaming]
-[Whinnying]

15:31.056 --> 15:33.433
All in favor of getting back
in the boat, say "aye."

15:33.559 --> 15:36.395
-Aye!
-Aye! Go!
-[Nickers]

15:49.700 --> 15:53.829
Hey, Miguel!
I could use a little help!

15:55.122 --> 15:57.416
Miguel!
Hello!

15:57.541 --> 15:59.209
Tulio!
We've done it!

15:59.293 --> 16:02.963
-What's that? The map?
-It's all right here!

16:03.046 --> 16:05.799
You still have the map?

16:05.924 --> 16:07.885
The whistling rock!
The stream!

16:07.968 --> 16:10.888
You kept the map, but you couldn't grab
a little more food?

16:11.013 --> 16:13.348
Even those mountains.
You said so yourself:

16:13.432 --> 16:16.769
It could be possible.
And it is!

16:16.852 --> 16:21.815
It really is... the map to El Dorado!
[Panting]

16:23.150 --> 16:25.778
-You drank seawater, didn't you?
-Oh, come on!

16:25.903 --> 16:27.780
I'm not coming on!

16:27.905 --> 16:31.408
I wouldn't set foot in that jungle
for a million pesetas!

16:31.533 --> 16:35.996
-How about a hundred million?
-What?

16:36.121 --> 16:39.666
I just thought that, after all,
since El Dorado is the city of gold--

16:39.792 --> 16:43.170
-What's your point?
-You know, dust, nuggets, bricks,

16:43.253 --> 16:46.131
a temple of gold where you can
pluck gold from the very walls.

16:46.215 --> 16:48.133
But you don't want to go, so let's...

16:48.258 --> 16:50.511
get back into the boat
and row back to Spain.

16:50.636 --> 16:54.139
-After all, it worked so well last time.
-[Gibberish] Wait!

16:54.264 --> 16:57.893
Mmm. Wait a minute.
New plan.

16:58.018 --> 17:02.439
We find the city of gold.
We take the gold,

17:02.564 --> 17:05.526
-and then we go back to Spain.
-And buy Spain!

17:05.608 --> 17:07.569
-Yeah!
-That's the spirit!

17:07.611 --> 17:13.075
-Come on, Tulio.
We'll follow that trail!
-What trail?

17:13.200 --> 17:18.579
The trail that we blaze!

17:18.664 --> 17:20.582
[Nickers]

17:20.707 --> 17:23.252
That trail that we blaze!

17:23.377 --> 17:25.921
-[Mutters]
-[Whinnies]

17:27.506 --> 17:29.800
Oh, no, you don't.

17:30.926 --> 17:34.471
Yeow! Your horse
bit me in the butt!

17:34.555 --> 17:38.475
-[Chittering]
-[Hissing]

17:38.559 --> 17:42.229
Look out new world
Here we come

17:42.354 --> 17:45.774
-Brave, intrepid
-Charge!

17:45.858 --> 17:48.277
And then some

17:50.154 --> 17:53.449
Pioneers of maximum audacity

17:53.574 --> 17:58.370
Whose résumés show
that we are just the team

17:58.454 --> 18:02.541
-To live where others merely dream
-What are you looking at?

18:02.666 --> 18:05.544
-Building up our head of steam
-Whoa!

18:05.669 --> 18:08.589
On the trail we blaze

18:08.714 --> 18:12.509
[Chorus Vocalizing]

18:12.593 --> 18:16.221
Changing legend into fact

18:16.347 --> 18:18.515
We shall ride into history

18:18.599 --> 18:21.393
Turning myth into truth

18:21.518 --> 18:24.438
We shall surely gaze

18:24.563 --> 18:28.776
On the sweet unfolding

18:28.859 --> 18:31.111
Of an antique mystery

18:31.236 --> 18:34.031
All will be revealed

18:34.114 --> 18:38.035
On the trail we blaze

18:38.118 --> 18:40.454
Oh! Oh!
Oh! Oh! Oh!

18:40.537 --> 18:43.582
[Chorus] On the trail
On the trail we blaze

18:43.707 --> 18:46.669
-Dinner is served.
-Hello.

18:46.752 --> 18:50.255
Paradise is close at hand

18:51.882 --> 18:53.842
Shangri-la

18:53.967 --> 18:56.887
The promised land

18:57.971 --> 19:01.308
Seventh heaven on demand

19:01.433 --> 19:03.686
Quite unusual nowadays

19:03.769 --> 19:06.814
Virgin vistas undefiled

19:06.897 --> 19:10.192
Minds and bodies running wild

19:10.317 --> 19:13.696
In the man behold a child

19:13.779 --> 19:16.156
On the trail we blaze

19:16.281 --> 19:18.909
[Chorus Vocalizing]

19:18.993 --> 19:21.245
[Chorus]
On the trail we blaze

19:21.328 --> 19:24.373
The trail we blaze

19:24.498 --> 19:26.542
Is road uncharted

19:26.625 --> 19:32.506
Through terra incognita
to a golden shrine

19:32.631 --> 19:35.843
No place for the traveler

19:35.968 --> 19:39.638
To be fainthearted

19:39.763 --> 19:44.643
We are part
of a sumptuous grand design

19:44.727 --> 19:47.313
Changing legend into fact

19:47.438 --> 19:50.858
We shall ride into history

19:50.983 --> 19:53.360
Turning myth into truth

19:53.444 --> 19:56.363
We shall surely gaze

19:56.447 --> 19:59.825
On the sweet unfolding

19:59.950 --> 20:02.995
Of an antique mystery

20:03.120 --> 20:05.539
All will be revealed

20:07.458 --> 20:09.752
[Creaking, Crackling]

20:11.086 --> 20:13.088
-On the trail we blaze
-[Yelling]

20:13.213 --> 20:16.133
[Yelling Continues]

20:17.259 --> 20:19.553
[All Grunting]

20:19.678 --> 20:21.555
[Groaning]

20:43.077 --> 20:45.037
Hmm.

20:47.623 --> 20:51.835
-[Snaps Fingers]
Miguel. Miguel, wake up.
-[Moans]

20:51.919 --> 20:55.464
-We're there. Oh, yeah. We found it.
-We found it? Oh!

20:55.589 --> 20:58.008
Fantastic!
Where is it? How far?

20:58.092 --> 20:59.969
-Right here! Here.
-Where? Behind the rock?

21:00.094 --> 21:01.929
-No, no. This is it.
-[Stammering]

21:02.012 --> 21:05.474
Give me that!
This ca-What?

21:05.599 --> 21:08.978
-Apparently, "El Dorado" is
native for...
-[Muttering]

21:09.061 --> 21:12.439
"great, big... rock"!

21:12.564 --> 21:16.277
[Echoing]

21:16.402 --> 21:21.323
Hey, but I tell you what, I'm feeling
generous, so you can have my share!

21:21.448 --> 21:24.785
You don't think Cortes could've
gotten here before us and--

21:24.910 --> 21:26.870
And what?
Taken all the really big rocks?

21:26.996 --> 21:29.290
-The scoundrel!
-Tulio, you--

21:29.415 --> 21:31.375
We have to think about this.
We've come all this way,

21:31.500 --> 21:34.420
-and we-we-we should really, you know--
-Get... on...

21:34.545 --> 21:36.755
the horse!

21:38.465 --> 21:40.509
[Sighs]

21:40.634 --> 21:43.929
No, no, no, not with the face.
Stop.

21:44.013 --> 21:48.142
[Clears Throat] Looks like
there's a pass right over there.

21:48.267 --> 21:50.519
[Panting] Ohh!

21:50.644 --> 21:52.855
[Panting Continues]

21:52.938 --> 21:56.442
-[Grunting, Gasps]
-[Whinnying]

21:58.319 --> 22:01.780
-[Men Shouting]
-[Both Gasping]

22:01.906 --> 22:04.283
-[Both] Hyah!
-[Whinnying]

22:05.576 --> 22:07.369
-[All Gasping]
-[Snorting]

22:14.335 --> 22:16.003
[Gasping, Grunting]

22:20.424 --> 22:23.969
[Chuckles] I've--

22:24.053 --> 22:26.847
Uh, hello. Is this your rock?

22:26.889 --> 22:28.849
Sorry. We were just looking.
We're, uh--

22:28.891 --> 22:30.809
We're tourists!
Tourist.

22:30.893 --> 22:34.688
-[Clears Throat]
-We-We lost our group. May we go now?

22:34.772 --> 22:38.108
-[Gasps]
-[Chuckles] Spears.

22:38.192 --> 22:39.693
[Grunts]

22:41.028 --> 22:43.822
[Nickers]

22:46.992 --> 22:48.911
[Chittering]

22:52.289 --> 22:54.250
Hey! Hey!

22:54.375 --> 22:56.377
-[Chittering]
-[Bird Calling]

22:57.878 --> 22:59.880
[Bird Calling Continues]

23:24.154 --> 23:26.031
[Sighs Dejectedly]

23:26.156 --> 23:28.742
[Whistling]

23:48.554 --> 23:50.681
[Gasps]

23:52.391 --> 23:55.311
[Gasps]

23:55.436 --> 23:57.980
Oh, my--

24:00.274 --> 24:02.109
[Miguel]
It's-It's--[Gasps]

24:02.234 --> 24:05.029
[Both Whispering]
El Dorado.

24:35.351 --> 24:37.311
-[Giggling]
-Oh!

24:43.442 --> 24:46.070
[Chittering]

24:57.581 --> 25:00.543
-[Chuckling]
-[Children Giggling]

25:00.668 --> 25:02.503
[Whispering]

25:06.006 --> 25:07.591
[Chanting]

25:09.718 --> 25:12.054
[Whispering]

25:12.138 --> 25:15.474
Mmm. Ah!

25:18.644 --> 25:20.896
[Chattering]

25:23.149 --> 25:27.695
[Sighs] Well, it was nice
working with you, partner.

25:27.820 --> 25:29.947
Tulio, I just want you to know...

25:30.030 --> 25:32.032
I'm sorry about
that girl in Barcelona.

25:32.158 --> 25:35.077
-So-You-You, f--
-[Man]Behold!

25:35.202 --> 25:37.663
As the prophesies foretold,

25:37.788 --> 25:41.333
the time of judgment is now!

25:41.459 --> 25:43.586
[Both Gasping]

25:47.089 --> 25:51.927
Citizens, did I not predict
that the gods would come to us?

25:54.180 --> 25:56.098
Hmm.

25:56.182 --> 25:59.769
[Chuckling]
My lords, I am Tzekel-Kan,

25:59.894 --> 26:03.564
your devoted high priest
and speaker for the gods.

26:03.647 --> 26:05.941
Hey.

26:06.025 --> 26:10.446
I am Chief Tannabok.
What names may we call you?

26:10.529 --> 26:14.366
-Huh? I am Miguel.
-[Murmuring]

26:14.450 --> 26:16.660
-And I am Tulio.
-[Murmuring Continues]

26:18.037 --> 26:20.289
And they call us Miguel and Tulio!

26:20.414 --> 26:23.542
[Tzekel-Kan] Your arrival
has been greatly anticipated.

26:23.667 --> 26:26.003
My lords, how long
will you be staying in El Dorado?

26:26.128 --> 26:31.092
-[Whimpering]
-Aha! I see you've captured
this temple-robbing thief.

26:31.217 --> 26:34.553
-How would you have us punish her?
-Oh, no, no, no, no, no!

26:34.678 --> 26:37.473
My lord, I am not a thief.

26:37.598 --> 26:40.142
See, the gods sent me a vision...

26:40.267 --> 26:42.978
to bring them tribute
from the temple to guide them here.

26:43.104 --> 26:47.817
My only wish is to serve the gods.

26:53.072 --> 26:55.616
-Release her, don't ya think?
-[Villagers Gasp]

26:55.741 --> 26:59.161
-[Grunts]
-Then you will begin
by returning this...

26:59.286 --> 27:02.289
to its rightful place.

27:02.373 --> 27:04.333
[Chittering]

27:04.458 --> 27:07.753
-My lords, why now
do you choose to visit us?
-[Scoffs]

27:07.878 --> 27:11.132
Enough!
You do not question... the gods!

27:11.215 --> 27:13.718
That's right!
Do not question us,

27:13.801 --> 27:18.305
or we shall have to unleash
our awesome and terrible power!

27:18.431 --> 27:20.683
And you don't want that!

27:20.808 --> 27:24.311
-Well, yes! We do!
-You do?

27:24.437 --> 27:28.232
Of course we do!
Visit your wrath upon this nonbeliever!

27:28.315 --> 27:30.693
Show us the truth
of your divinity!

27:30.776 --> 27:33.446
-Divinity! One moment.
-[Chuckles]

27:37.742 --> 27:39.744
Miguel, you know
that little voice people have...

27:39.827 --> 27:41.746
that tells them to quit
when they're ahead?

27:41.829 --> 27:44.623
-You don't have one!
-Well, I'm sorry. I got carried away!

27:44.749 --> 27:48.377
-Way away!
-Maybe we should tell
the truth and beg for mercy.

27:48.502 --> 27:50.171
Are you nuts?
We'd be butchered alive!

27:50.296 --> 27:52.298
Yes, but they're getting suspicious.

27:52.423 --> 27:55.009
-And if we don't come up
with so me mega-cosmic event--
-[Rumbling]

27:55.134 --> 27:57.845
-[Altivo Whinnying]
-[Chittering]

27:57.928 --> 28:00.431
I'm trying! I'm trying! I can't think
with all these distractions!

28:00.514 --> 28:03.601
-You-Horse--
-Think horse. Think, think, think.

28:03.726 --> 28:08.689
I'm on the verge of--
Stop! [Echoing]

28:11.817 --> 28:14.987
[Coughing Sound]

28:15.112 --> 28:17.657
-[Gasps]
-[Gasps]

28:20.201 --> 28:22.578
[Crickets Chirping]

28:30.878 --> 28:33.631
[Villagers Chanting]

28:33.714 --> 28:37.218
-[Chanting Continues]
-Don't make me start it up again,

28:37.343 --> 28:39.553
'cause I will.

28:39.679 --> 28:42.515
[Chanting Continues]

28:44.558 --> 28:48.187
O mighty lords!

28:48.312 --> 28:50.648
Come.
Let me show you to your temple.

28:50.731 --> 28:52.942
All right!
Temple.

28:56.028 --> 28:58.406
Step aside.

29:00.282 --> 29:02.118
[Villagers Murmuring]

29:17.258 --> 29:20.553
[Panting]

29:20.678 --> 29:23.806
[Grunting]

29:23.889 --> 29:26.726
[Panting Continues]

29:32.189 --> 29:34.066
[Sputters]

29:41.198 --> 29:45.828
To commemorate your arrival,
I propose a reverent ceremony at dawn.

29:45.911 --> 29:51.667
Ah, then perhaps I could prepare
a glorious feast for you tonight.

29:51.751 --> 29:54.545
Which would you prefer?

29:55.921 --> 29:57.965
-Both.
-Both.
-[Together] Both.

29:58.049 --> 30:00.009
Both is good.

30:00.051 --> 30:03.679
-My lords.
-My lords.

30:06.599 --> 30:10.436
And so dawns the Age of the Jaguar.

30:12.146 --> 30:14.482
Happy New Year.
[Chuckles]

30:20.821 --> 30:23.491
-Hey!
-Hey. Hey.

30:23.574 --> 30:26.035
-[Laughing]
-[Laughing]

30:26.160 --> 30:28.663
[Whinnying]

30:28.788 --> 30:33.626
Tulio. Tulio.
They actually think we're gods.

30:33.751 --> 30:37.588
-[Tulio]
It's an entire city of suckers.
-[Miguel Laughing]

30:37.672 --> 30:39.632
We just have to keep
this up long enough...

30:39.757 --> 30:43.135
to load up on the gold
and then get the hell out of here!

30:43.261 --> 30:45.763
Tulio, we'll be living like kings!

30:45.888 --> 30:48.557
-Miguel and Tulio!
-Tulio and Miguel!

30:48.683 --> 30:51.310
-Mighty and powerful gods.
-Gods.

30:51.435 --> 30:54.355
-Hello.
-[Both Gasping, Whimpering]

30:54.480 --> 30:57.441
-[Laughing]
-Depart, mortal,

30:57.567 --> 31:00.570
-before we strike you
with a lightning bolt.
-Mmm. Mmmm!

31:00.653 --> 31:02.363
[Humming]

31:02.488 --> 31:05.366
Beware the wrath of the gods! Begone!
[Clicking Sound]

31:05.449 --> 31:08.536
Save it for the high priest, honey.
You're gonna need it.

31:08.619 --> 31:10.955
-[Clicking Sound]
-Miguel, it's not working.

31:11.038 --> 31:13.541
-[Clicking Sound]
-Miguel! We've been caught.

31:13.624 --> 31:16.168
Oh, no.
Don't worry about me, boys.

31:16.252 --> 31:20.506
"My only wish is to serve the gods."
Remember?

31:20.631 --> 31:23.843
-How?
-Well, if you guys want the gold,

31:23.926 --> 31:25.970
then you don't want
to get caught, right?

31:26.095 --> 31:30.016
-You're going to need my help.
-[Scoffs] What makes you
think we need your help?

31:31.350 --> 31:34.312
-"Ck-ck." Are you serious?
-[Whinnies]

31:34.395 --> 31:37.398
I-What-We--

31:37.481 --> 31:40.276
Okay. So, uh, who are you?

31:40.401 --> 31:43.571
-Yeah, uh, what's your angle?
-[Laughs] No angle.

31:43.654 --> 31:46.282
-I want in.
-In?

31:46.407 --> 31:49.243
-On the scam.
-[Chuckles]

31:49.327 --> 31:51.537
There's no scam!
Why would you think there's a--

31:51.662 --> 31:54.707
-Why?
-So I can get out.

31:54.832 --> 31:57.001
I thought she just said she wanted in?

31:57.126 --> 31:59.420
She wants in so she can get out.

31:59.503 --> 32:02.465
Aha! Got it.
[Chuckles]

32:02.548 --> 32:06.510
-W-Why?
-Think you're the only ones
who dream of better things?

32:06.636 --> 32:10.306
Of adventure?
You've got your reasons,

32:10.389 --> 32:12.308
and I've got mine.

32:12.391 --> 32:14.810
Let's not make it personal, okay?

32:14.936 --> 32:18.356
-It's just business.
-[Both] Oh.

32:18.439 --> 32:21.484
So when you guys
are ready to go back to...

32:21.609 --> 32:23.778
wherever you came from,

32:23.861 --> 32:26.239
-I'm going with you.
-[Laughs]

32:26.322 --> 32:29.283
No!
Don't think so.

32:29.367 --> 32:31.285
[Coughs]

32:31.369 --> 32:33.496
-[Whistling]
-All right. Fine.

32:33.621 --> 32:35.498
After all, I'm sure you know...

32:35.623 --> 32:38.709
the proper rituals
for blessing a tribute,
the holiest days on the calendar--

32:38.793 --> 32:42.755
Oh, and of course you know
all about Xibalba.

32:42.839 --> 32:45.925
[Chuckles]
Okay? Good luck.

32:48.553 --> 32:51.931
-See you at the execution.
-[Gibberish]

32:52.014 --> 32:54.433
Wait! Ho--
Would you-Hold it.

32:58.855 --> 33:01.649
-[Chuckles] Deal?
-Hmm.

33:01.732 --> 33:05.486
-Deal.
-Not yet.
Let's just see how this works out.

33:05.570 --> 33:09.866
Uh-huh. Well, then I suppose that means
you'll want these back?

33:11.868 --> 33:14.954
-How'd you get those?
-Where was she keeping them?

33:15.079 --> 33:18.666
-Call me, Chel, your new partner.
-Uh,

33:18.791 --> 33:20.668
-that's partner-in-training.
-[Humming]

33:20.793 --> 33:22.753
Now, put these on.

33:22.879 --> 33:25.089
Your public's waiting.
[Continues]

33:26.257 --> 33:28.384
-[Chel Giggling]
-Do you mind?

33:28.509 --> 33:30.428
No.

33:30.511 --> 33:32.430
Oh! Oh! Oh!
[Giggles]

33:32.513 --> 33:34.599
Right. Uh, excuse me.

33:34.724 --> 33:37.852
-[Grunting]
-Bye.

33:40.062 --> 33:43.941
Mm-mm-mmm! Maybe they should call
this place "Chel Dorado."

33:44.025 --> 33:47.069
[Chuckles]
She's whoo--

33:47.153 --> 33:49.280
-Whoa, she's trouble! Wait a minute!
-What?

33:49.405 --> 33:51.532
The little voice--
Remember the little voice?

33:51.616 --> 33:54.702
Ju-Ju-Just for a second
imagine that you have one.

33:54.827 --> 33:57.371
What would it be saying about Chel?

33:58.539 --> 34:01.417
-[Purrs]
-No. No. Listen.

34:01.501 --> 34:03.419
-We are partners.
-We are partners.

34:03.503 --> 34:07.215
-We have a plan, remember?
-Get the gold. Go back to Spain.

34:07.340 --> 34:10.510
Yes! And we are
pretending to be gods.

34:10.635 --> 34:13.596
Now, put Chel in the mix.
What is the voice saying?

34:13.721 --> 34:17.308
-Listen carefully.
-[Gasps]

34:17.391 --> 34:22.730
-Chel is off-limits, hmm?
-Bravo! Chel is off-limits!

34:22.813 --> 34:24.732
Shake on it.

34:24.815 --> 34:27.610
-Off-limits. Mm. Mm.
-[Both] Mmmm.

34:27.735 --> 34:30.071
Besides, we're supposed to be gods.

34:30.196 --> 34:32.281
We must avoid
giving in to temptation.

34:32.406 --> 34:38.246
-Gods. Oh. This is
gonna be tougher than I thought.
-Tulio, relax!

34:38.329 --> 34:42.917
All you have to do is smile,
act godly and follow my lead.

34:43.042 --> 34:45.420
[Gasps]

34:46.295 --> 34:48.965
[Gasps] Big smile.
Like you mean it.

34:49.090 --> 34:51.050
A-one, two, three.

34:55.804 --> 34:59.725
I hardly think I'm qualified

34:59.809 --> 35:02.603
To come across all sanctified

35:02.728 --> 35:06.607
I just don't cut it
with the cherubim

35:06.649 --> 35:09.277
-[Groaning]
-Tulio, what are you talking about?

35:09.402 --> 35:12.405
There again they're on their knees

35:12.488 --> 35:15.032
Being worshipped is a breeze

35:15.116 --> 35:17.744
Which rather suits us in

35:17.869 --> 35:21.914
-The interim
-Interim, interim
It's me and him

35:22.039 --> 35:25.209
Oh, my God!
It's tough to be a god

35:25.334 --> 35:29.338
Tread where mortals have not trod

35:29.464 --> 35:34.177
Be deified when really you're a sham

35:35.887 --> 35:38.848
Be an object of devotion

35:38.890 --> 35:41.851
Be the subject of psalms

35:41.976 --> 35:44.854
It's a rather touching notion

35:44.979 --> 35:48.232
All those prayers and those salaams

35:48.316 --> 35:51.569
And who am I to bridle

35:51.694 --> 35:54.030
If I'm forced to be an idol

35:54.113 --> 35:57.408
If they say that I'm a god

35:57.492 --> 35:59.619
That's what I am

35:59.744 --> 36:02.997
What's more if we don't comply

36:03.122 --> 36:05.166
With the locals' wishes

36:05.249 --> 36:09.379
I can see us being sacrificed

36:09.504 --> 36:11.839
-Or stuffed
-You have a point there.
Very good thinking.

36:11.964 --> 36:15.676
-So let's be gods
The perks are great
-Yeah!

36:15.802 --> 36:18.721
-El Dorado on our plates
-Thank you.

36:18.846 --> 36:20.932
Local feelings should not

36:21.057 --> 36:22.934
-Be rebuffed
-Never rebuffed

36:23.059 --> 36:26.729
I never rebuff a local feeling
No, my friend

36:26.854 --> 36:28.898
It's tough to be a god

36:29.023 --> 36:32.443
But if you get the people's nod

36:32.568 --> 36:35.113
Count your blessings
Yeah, keep 'em sweet

36:35.196 --> 36:38.908
-That's our advice
-It's great advice!

36:38.991 --> 36:41.994
Be a symbol of perfection

36:42.120 --> 36:45.206
Be a legend
Be a cult

36:45.289 --> 36:48.042
Take their praise
Take a collection

36:48.126 --> 36:51.045
As the multitudes exalt

36:51.129 --> 36:54.257
Don a supernatural habit

36:54.382 --> 36:57.677
-We'd be crazy not to grab it
-You got it!

36:57.760 --> 37:00.054
So sign on two new gods

37:00.138 --> 37:02.849
For paradise

37:02.932 --> 37:06.978
Par-a-dise

37:07.103 --> 37:09.313
-[Continues]
-[Chattering, Laughing]

37:12.025 --> 37:15.153
-[Screeching]
-[Drunken Whinnying]

37:20.783 --> 37:22.660
[Fades, Ends]

37:23.786 --> 37:27.665
[Both Snoring, Mumbling]

37:31.753 --> 37:34.547
-[Metallic Clattering]
-[Both Gasping]

37:34.672 --> 37:37.550
Good morning, my lords!

37:37.675 --> 37:41.596
-He's back!
-Oh, no.

37:44.766 --> 37:46.934
And now it's my turn!

37:49.979 --> 37:54.984
-The gods have awakened!
-[Cheering]

37:55.068 --> 37:56.986
Whoa!
[Groans]

37:57.070 --> 37:59.489
Mm-hmm.

37:59.614 --> 38:02.116
-[Grunts]
-[Whimpering]

38:02.241 --> 38:06.496
-Hey, Chel, what's going on?
-It's not gonna be good.

38:06.579 --> 38:08.581
Thank you.

38:08.706 --> 38:11.292
This city has been granted
a great blessing.

38:11.376 --> 38:16.214
And what have we done
to show our gratitude?

38:16.339 --> 38:19.467
A meager celebration.

38:19.592 --> 38:24.013
-The gods deserve a proper tribute!
-[Crowd Gasping]

38:25.223 --> 38:27.725
-Hmm.
-Hmm.

38:27.809 --> 38:32.689
The beginning of a new era,
the dawning of a new age...

38:32.814 --> 38:35.775
demands...

38:35.900 --> 38:38.236
sacrifice!

38:38.319 --> 38:40.238
-[All Gasping]
-[Gasps]

38:44.826 --> 38:47.996
-I don't like this.
-Tulio, we've got to do something.

38:48.121 --> 38:50.415
[Groans]

38:54.794 --> 38:57.005
-[Groaning]
-[Yells]

38:57.130 --> 38:59.549
[Tulio]Stop!

38:59.632 --> 39:02.051
Hmm?

39:04.012 --> 39:06.681
-This is not a proper tribute!
-[Moaning]

39:06.806 --> 39:08.808
-[Crowd Gasps]
-You do not want the tribute?

39:08.891 --> 39:10.810
No. No, no.
W-We want tribute.

39:10.893 --> 39:14.856
Uh, it's just that, uh--
Tulio, tell him.

39:17.025 --> 39:21.154
The stars are not in position
for this tribute!

39:21.279 --> 39:23.615
Like he says, the stars--

39:23.740 --> 39:25.742
Can't do it.

39:25.867 --> 39:27.785
Not today.

39:31.456 --> 39:33.374
Ah.

39:33.458 --> 39:37.128
Perhaps it is possible
I misread... the heavens.

39:37.211 --> 39:41.215
-Don't worry about it.
To err is human, to forgive--
-Hmm.

39:41.341 --> 39:46.179
My lords, may the people of El Dorado
offer you our tribute.

39:47.305 --> 39:49.349
[Crowd Gasping]

39:50.767 --> 39:52.644
[Gasps]

39:52.769 --> 39:55.647
[Gasping Continues]

39:56.898 --> 39:59.776
My lords, does this please you?

39:59.859 --> 40:02.612
-[Sighs]
-Yes, very nice.

40:02.737 --> 40:04.614
-Certainly acceptable.
-Yes, lovely. It'll do.

40:04.739 --> 40:07.575
The gods have chosen!

40:07.659 --> 40:09.577
To Xibalba?

40:09.661 --> 40:12.622
-[Crowd Murmuring]
-No. No.

40:12.705 --> 40:15.124
[Together] To Xibalba!

40:15.250 --> 40:17.126
-[Crowd Cheering]
-Oh, great.

40:18.503 --> 40:21.422
[Cheering Continues]

40:31.432 --> 40:34.644
Hey, Chel, um,
what are they doing?

40:34.769 --> 40:38.147
They're sending it to Xibalba,
the spirit world.

40:39.816 --> 40:42.610
-The spirit world.
-I'll take care of it.

40:44.320 --> 40:47.073
[Clears Throat]
Um, excuse me, Chief.

40:47.198 --> 40:49.867
The gods have changed their minds
about Xibalba.

40:52.745 --> 40:57.166
They wish to bask in the reverence
that has been shown them.

40:57.250 --> 40:58.585
Stop!

41:02.422 --> 41:06.259
-[Crowd Murmuring]
-They wish to bask!

41:06.384 --> 41:09.554
Take the tribute to the gods' temple!

41:09.637 --> 41:12.265
-[Crowd Cheering]
-[Humming]

41:12.390 --> 41:14.392
Nice going.

41:20.982 --> 41:22.859
[Chuckles]

41:24.319 --> 41:26.654
Smile while you can.

41:37.624 --> 41:41.169
Well, well, well,

41:41.211 --> 41:43.880
what have we here?

41:44.005 --> 41:46.174
[Evil Chuckle]

41:46.299 --> 41:48.885
-[Tulio]Ai-ai-ai.
-Tons of gold for you, hah

41:49.010 --> 41:52.430
-And tons of gold for me, hoo
-[Together]
Tons of gold for we, ah

41:52.555 --> 41:55.683
-Not bad for a day's work, eh?
-Not bad at all.

41:55.808 --> 41:59.354
We just became richer
than the king of Spain. [Laughing]

41:59.479 --> 42:05.109
You know, speaking of kings, the chief
and high priest seem a bit, uh, tense.

42:05.193 --> 42:07.278
Buenos días!

42:07.362 --> 42:09.739
Listen, all we have to do...

42:09.864 --> 42:14.202
is keep playing
the one against the other.

42:14.285 --> 42:17.205
You know, do a little god dance,
chant some mystic mumbo jumbo,

42:17.288 --> 42:19.749
dazzle 'em with some smoke and mirrors
and then get the hell back to Spain.

42:19.874 --> 42:24.838
Um, Tulio, how are we gonna
get all this back to Spain?

42:24.963 --> 42:27.507
Ummm--

42:27.632 --> 42:29.759
-A boat?
-[Tulio] Yeah.

42:29.884 --> 42:32.887
Um, we really hate
to be ascending so soon,

42:32.929 --> 42:35.473
but, uh, some urgent business
has come up--

42:35.598 --> 42:37.767
-family matters-and it's just a bit--
-Yeah, family.

42:37.851 --> 42:39.769
Badda-bing, budda-boom,
you know what I mean.

42:39.853 --> 42:42.897
Oh, we expected you
to be staying with us...

42:43.022 --> 42:45.859
for the next...
thousand years.

42:45.984 --> 42:48.111
Well, as we say
in the spirit world,

42:48.194 --> 42:51.781
-there's your plan and then...
there's the gods' plan.
-Mm-hmm.

42:51.906 --> 42:54.742
And our plan, uh, calls for a boat,
'cause we're gonna ascend...

42:54.826 --> 42:57.370
-kind of in
a horizontal pattern at first.
-[Chuckles]

42:57.495 --> 43:01.458
And then we're gonna go vertical,
uh, as we get further out to sea.

43:01.541 --> 43:04.752
Hmm. To build a boat
large and glorious enough...

43:04.878 --> 43:07.464
would take... about a week.

43:07.589 --> 43:10.216
-A week? Hmm.
-Um--

43:10.341 --> 43:13.386
I wonder how long it would take
Tzekel-Kan to do it.

43:13.511 --> 43:17.265
But-But for the gods,
uh, three days.

43:17.390 --> 43:19.267
Uh--

43:19.392 --> 43:22.145
Well, if that's the best you can do.

43:22.228 --> 43:26.399
Oh, perhaps if you were not burdened
with so much tribute,

43:26.524 --> 43:28.443
you could leave sooner.

43:28.526 --> 43:31.154
-Hmm?
-Hmm? I like it here. Miguel?

43:31.279 --> 43:34.449
Yep, yep.
Three days is just fine.

43:34.574 --> 43:37.035
-[Tulio]No, three days is not fine.
-[Chel Humming]

43:37.118 --> 43:40.705
-This is a real--
-Mmm.

43:40.830 --> 43:45.043
-these-these are the ones-problem.
-Oh. Thank you.

43:45.168 --> 43:48.171
-Miguel, how are we gonna
keep this up for three days?
-[Yawns]

43:48.296 --> 43:50.256
You worry too much.

43:50.381 --> 43:52.550
No, I worry exactly the right amount.

43:52.675 --> 43:55.845
You can never worry too much.

43:55.929 --> 43:58.640
We just have to lie low.

43:58.765 --> 44:04.145
But, Tulio, this place is amazing!
I mean, I wonder what's--

44:04.270 --> 44:06.689
No! Don't even move!

44:06.731 --> 44:08.650
-Tulio--
-You're moving!

44:08.691 --> 44:10.860
-A little, but-Come on.
-Hey! Hey! Hey!

44:10.985 --> 44:13.071
-[Stammering] Stay!
-I gotta-I--

44:13.154 --> 44:17.408
-[Groans]Just... stand there!
-I just--

44:18.827 --> 44:21.162
For three days?

44:21.287 --> 44:23.289
-[Clatter]
-Yes! Exactly.

44:23.373 --> 44:27.502
For three days.
Don't even breathe. All right?

44:28.837 --> 44:30.755
All right.
We lie low.

44:30.839 --> 44:32.882
No, ah, ah, ah, ah.
Promise?

44:33.007 --> 44:34.884
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
All right, all right.

44:35.009 --> 44:38.388
Great! Good. Okay.

44:38.471 --> 44:41.891
-Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have to gloat over my gold.
-[Giggling]

44:43.852 --> 44:46.396
[Kissing]

44:46.521 --> 44:49.190
Oh, yum, yum, yum.

44:49.315 --> 44:51.735
[Kissing Continues]

44:51.818 --> 44:54.738
-It's beautiful, isn't it?
-Yeah!

44:54.863 --> 44:58.241
-You know, you really shouldn't miss it.
-I know.

44:58.366 --> 45:00.535
But I-I couldn't.

45:00.660 --> 45:03.580
Go ahead.
I'll cover for you.

45:03.663 --> 45:07.625
-Oh, good. Thanks.
-[Tulio Singing, Indistinct]

45:07.709 --> 45:10.044
-So, what happened to Altivo?
-I don't know.

45:10.128 --> 45:13.882
Tulio goes for paradise

45:14.007 --> 45:17.385
-Hey, what happened to Miguel?
-I don't know.

45:17.510 --> 45:21.056
Oh, my God! He's gone!
Miguel's gone!

45:21.139 --> 45:23.391
He's loose!
What am I gonna do?

45:23.516 --> 45:27.103
Oh, no, no!
[Sobbing]

45:27.228 --> 45:30.690
Oh, Miguel is right.
You worry too much.

45:30.815 --> 45:32.776
[Groaning]

45:32.859 --> 45:35.945
Oh. Ooh.
[Moans]

45:36.071 --> 45:40.241
-Oh, yeah. Oh, oh, down, down, down.
-[Humming]

45:40.367 --> 45:43.286
-No! No! Big trouble.
-[Gasps]

45:43.370 --> 45:45.747
[Chuckling] Whoa!

45:45.872 --> 45:49.125
Look, sweetheart,
we're in the middle of a con here,

45:49.250 --> 45:51.461
walking the razor's edge.

45:51.586 --> 45:54.005
On the one hand, gold!

45:54.130 --> 45:58.635
On the other hand,
painful, agonizing failure!

45:58.760 --> 46:02.722
[Clears Throat] I can't afford
any tempta-uh, distractions.

46:02.847 --> 46:06.142
So, I'm sorry.
So sorry.

46:06.226 --> 46:09.938
[Sharp Inhale] But perhaps
another time? Another place, hmm?

46:10.021 --> 46:13.441
[Chuckles]
Too bad. I'm free now.

46:14.984 --> 46:18.571
I'm... not really sure
I trust you.

46:18.655 --> 46:21.616
Mmm, I'm not really
asking you to trust me.

46:21.700 --> 46:24.994
-Am I?
-Whoo.

46:25.120 --> 46:27.080
'Kay.

46:27.205 --> 46:29.124
[Moans]

46:29.207 --> 46:31.292
Ooh, yeah.

46:37.090 --> 46:39.634
[Chirping]

46:53.481 --> 46:55.859
Excuse me.
Excuse me?

46:57.068 --> 46:59.779
Hey, where is everybody?

46:59.904 --> 47:02.073
They've been cleared
from the streets, my lord,

47:02.157 --> 47:05.452
so the city can be cleansed,
as you ordered.

47:05.535 --> 47:07.620
-Cleansed?
-Yes.

47:07.746 --> 47:11.041
So the Age of the Jaguar can begin,

47:11.166 --> 47:13.043
-as you ordered, my lord.
-[Man]Get back in!

47:13.168 --> 47:15.086
-Where are you going?
-Hey, stop that!

47:15.170 --> 47:17.047
-[Guard]Move!
-Hey, stop that!

47:17.130 --> 47:19.382
What are you doing?
Stop that!

47:19.466 --> 47:21.593
But, my lord,
anyone who disobeys your orders...

47:21.718 --> 47:24.512
must be punished, as you ordered.

47:24.638 --> 47:27.724
It seems I've been giving
a lot of orders, haven't I?

47:27.849 --> 47:30.393
Tzekel-Kan has made
your commands clear, my lord.

47:30.518 --> 47:32.687
Really?

47:32.729 --> 47:36.149
-Here's an order: Take the day off.
-Huh?

47:37.359 --> 47:40.737
-Are you all right?
-[Panting]

47:40.862 --> 47:42.989
-Here.
-[Whimpers]

47:44.783 --> 47:48.370
Oh, no!
It's all right. Please.

47:50.872 --> 47:54.125
[Random Notes]

47:55.710 --> 47:57.963
[Tuning]

48:00.090 --> 48:01.257
[Continues]

48:01.383 --> 48:04.886
-[Whinnies]
-Hey, Altivo. There you are.

48:04.970 --> 48:07.347
-[Gasps]
-[Strums]

48:07.472 --> 48:09.349
[Playing A Tune]

48:09.474 --> 48:12.227
-Oh.
-Oh.

48:15.230 --> 48:18.149
[Both Chuckling]

48:18.275 --> 48:19.859
[Murmuring]

48:22.404 --> 48:24.906
[Continues]

48:27.409 --> 48:30.078
The more I learn

48:30.203 --> 48:33.081
The more I see

48:34.874 --> 48:39.504
The less the world impassions me

48:41.923 --> 48:44.050
The hungry heart

48:45.260 --> 48:47.304
The roving eye

48:48.555 --> 48:50.557
Have come to rest

48:50.682 --> 48:53.226
Do not apply

48:56.021 --> 48:58.315
The frantic chase

48:59.566 --> 49:02.444
The crazy ride

49:02.527 --> 49:06.364
The thrill has gone

49:06.489 --> 49:09.492
I step aside

49:09.618 --> 49:11.119
I'd believe

49:11.244 --> 49:12.954
In anything

49:13.079 --> 49:15.457
Were it not for you

49:16.708 --> 49:20.295
Showing me by just existing

49:20.378 --> 49:23.381
Only this is true

49:23.506 --> 49:25.800
I love you

49:27.177 --> 49:29.971
I love you

49:30.055 --> 49:32.807
Without question

49:32.891 --> 49:34.601
I love you

49:34.726 --> 49:38.021
I'd believe in anything

49:38.146 --> 49:40.106
Were it not for you

49:41.691 --> 49:47.405
Showing me by just existing
Only this is true

49:47.530 --> 49:50.951
Oh, I love you

49:55.872 --> 49:57.832
[Chuckles]

49:59.000 --> 50:01.086
[All Chuckling]

50:08.343 --> 50:10.220
[Whinnies]

50:16.851 --> 50:21.898
Hmm. This is not what I expected.

50:23.108 --> 50:25.068
Perhaps Lord Tulio will enlighten me.

50:25.193 --> 50:27.654
[Chuckling]

50:27.737 --> 50:29.656
How do I look?

50:29.781 --> 50:33.076
Oh, uh-Well, you--

50:33.201 --> 50:35.120
Oh, shut up.

50:35.245 --> 50:37.873
-[Tulio Gasps]Oh! Whoa!
-[Chel Humming]

50:37.956 --> 50:39.833
-[Tzekel-Kan]My lord?
-[Gasps]

50:39.958 --> 50:42.836
-Hello?
-The high priest.
-Ow!

50:42.961 --> 50:46.882
[Gasps] What's he gonna think if he
finds one of the gods like this with me?

50:46.965 --> 50:49.050
Uh, lucky god?

50:49.134 --> 50:51.636
J-Just-Just-Just--
[Groans]

50:51.720 --> 50:53.638
-Hello?
-Whoa!

50:56.016 --> 50:57.934
Oh, Tzekel-Kan!

50:58.018 --> 51:03.231
-What brings you here?
-I-I-I-I-I humbly request
an audience with you, my lord.

51:03.356 --> 51:08.695
-Yes, what can I do for you?
-My lord, I have just seen
Lord Miguel out among the people.

51:08.778 --> 51:12.949
-Really?
-If I may be so bold as to
offer some advice.

51:13.033 --> 51:15.577
-All right. Shoot.
-[Clears Throat]

51:15.660 --> 51:17.996
My lord, you are perfect.

51:18.079 --> 51:20.290
[Chuckles]
Oh, well. Go on.

51:20.373 --> 51:25.587
But in your perfection, you cannot know
how imperfect humans are.

51:25.712 --> 51:30.842
-Like snakes they are.
Spineless and slippery.
-[Hissing]

51:30.967 --> 51:36.097
They are as untrustworthy as rats,
stealing and cheating with no remorse.

51:37.349 --> 51:41.645
Spinning webs of lies, like spiders!

51:41.770 --> 51:44.439
Stop it!
That's disgusting.

51:44.564 --> 51:47.192
They're beyond disgusting!

51:47.275 --> 51:50.487
-Yeah, yeah, way beyond.
-Then we're in agreement.

51:50.570 --> 51:52.989
I'll begin the necessary
preparations immediately.

51:53.073 --> 51:57.744
Do you wish to have
your victims bound to an altar,
or would you prefer them free-range?

51:57.869 --> 52:00.497
-[Mutters]
-And will you be devouring
their essence whole...

52:00.622 --> 52:03.416
or piece by piece?

52:03.542 --> 52:05.961
Tzekel, you've lost me.

52:06.086 --> 52:10.048
My lord, these people will not
respect you if they do not fear you.

52:10.132 --> 52:12.592
And, of course, we'll make them
fear us by--

52:12.717 --> 52:15.262
A sacrifice, as it is prophesied

52:15.387 --> 52:18.932
-The history of the Age
of the Jaguar will be written in--
-Ink?

52:19.015 --> 52:21.226
-Blood!
-Blood! Oh, right.

52:21.351 --> 52:24.020
Of course. I should probably
consult with Lord Miguel.

52:24.104 --> 52:28.066
This is fairly important stuff.
I, um, should discuss the entire, uh,

52:28.150 --> 52:31.611
blood issue right away.

52:31.695 --> 52:34.614
Excuse us, won't you?
Let's go.

52:34.698 --> 52:40.245
[Chuckles]
Finally... we're connecting.

52:40.370 --> 52:42.247
[Horse Whinnies]

52:43.665 --> 52:46.209
[Nickering]

52:49.254 --> 52:51.173
This way.

52:53.008 --> 52:55.886
-[Chief Laughing]
-[Chuckling, Panting]

52:57.429 --> 52:59.306
[Grunts]

52:59.431 --> 53:03.602
-What do you think you're doing?
-[Chuckles] Lying low.

53:03.727 --> 53:06.229
[Grunts]
Look, change of plans.

53:06.313 --> 53:10.525
-We have to grab what we can carry
and get out of here now!
-What? Why?

53:10.650 --> 53:12.861
Because the high priest is nuts!
He wants--

53:12.944 --> 53:15.447
-This is unacceptable!
-Yeah. Yeah. Like he said.

53:15.530 --> 53:18.992
The gods should not
be playing ball like this!

53:19.117 --> 53:23.789
-Well, exactly!
-This is how the gods should play ball!

53:23.872 --> 53:26.166
-[Cheering]
-[Horn Sounding]

53:27.876 --> 53:30.378
-Well, don't blame me.
-I blame you.

53:32.130 --> 53:35.717
What is the object of this game,
pray tell?

53:35.842 --> 53:37.719
You've gotta knock the ball
through the hoop.

53:37.844 --> 53:39.721
-What hoop?
-That hoop.

53:39.846 --> 53:42.724
-[Cheering Continues]
-That's impossible.

53:42.808 --> 53:45.268
-We're gonna lose.
-Gods don't lose.

53:46.937 --> 53:49.022
[Rumbling]

53:49.147 --> 53:51.024
[Men] Heep-ha!

53:51.149 --> 53:54.986
My lords, Chief Tannabok's warriors are
the finest ballplayers in the city.

53:55.070 --> 53:59.241
-[Grunting, Gargling]
-Fifteen mere mortals against two gods.

53:59.366 --> 54:00.909
[Both Gulp]

54:01.034 --> 54:02.911
-I realize it's a bit uneven,
-[Warriors] Heep-ha!

54:03.036 --> 54:07.624
but I do hope they'll challenge you
enough to make the game... interesting.

54:07.749 --> 54:09.668
-Play ball!
-[Crowd Cheering]

54:12.003 --> 54:14.965
Crush them into the dust.
[Chuckles]

54:15.090 --> 54:16.967
-Enjoy.
-[Crowd Chanting]Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!

54:17.050 --> 54:19.094
-[Rumbling]
-[Chanting, Cheering Continue]

54:23.849 --> 54:25.809
-[Yells]
-[Gasps]

54:25.892 --> 54:28.645
-D'oh. D'oh.
-[Murmuring]

54:28.770 --> 54:30.355
[All Grunting]

54:30.439 --> 54:32.941
My lords,

54:33.024 --> 54:36.361
were you not supposed
to put the ball into play?

54:36.486 --> 54:38.613
Ohh!
[Chuckles]

54:38.697 --> 54:40.657
Well, no, no, no, no, no--

54:40.782 --> 54:46.163
We were merely demonstrating
the, um, traditional, uh,
first avoidance maneuver.

54:46.288 --> 54:48.874
Ah.

54:48.957 --> 54:51.126
I've never heard
of such a thing.

54:51.209 --> 54:53.587
Excuse me.

54:53.712 --> 54:56.590
Who invented this game?

54:56.715 --> 55:01.094
-Why, the gods, [Chuckles] of course.
-[Chuckles]

55:01.178 --> 55:04.514
I'm warning you,
don't push your luck with this guy.

55:04.639 --> 55:08.477
But, Tulio, we're the gods.

55:08.602 --> 55:11.188
-[Crowd Cheering]
-[Grunts]

55:14.066 --> 55:16.234
Tulio!
The hip! The hip!

55:16.318 --> 55:18.195
[Groans]

55:19.696 --> 55:23.283
-[Panting] This is impossible.
-[Grunts]

55:23.367 --> 55:26.203
-[Cheering]
-[Groaning]

55:26.328 --> 55:28.955
-[Horn Sounds]
-Excuse me?

55:29.081 --> 55:32.376
-Heep--
-Haaa!

55:33.668 --> 55:36.004
Heep-ha! Heep-ha!
Heep-ha! Heep-ha!

55:36.129 --> 55:38.048
[Both Groan]

55:42.302 --> 55:46.223
-[Warriors Chanting]
-[Footsteps Rumbling]

55:46.306 --> 55:48.350
[Chel]
Foul! That was a foul!

55:48.475 --> 55:50.602
[Chanting Continues]

55:50.727 --> 55:52.979
-[Squeaks]
-[Gasps]

55:53.105 --> 55:56.525
[Warrior]
New ball!

55:56.608 --> 55:58.944
[Both Panting]

55:59.069 --> 56:01.029
How long does this go on anyway?

56:01.154 --> 56:03.699
The game is over
when the shadow touches this line.

56:03.782 --> 56:06.994
-We need a miracle.
-No, we need to cheat.

56:12.833 --> 56:15.585
-[Warriors Shouting]
-[Crowd Cheering]

56:16.670 --> 56:19.172
[Chittering]

56:23.218 --> 56:26.013
-[Both] Yes!
-[Horn Sounding]

56:28.974 --> 56:31.268
-[Both] Huh?
-[All Grunting]

56:31.351 --> 56:33.478
Hey!

56:33.562 --> 56:36.106
-[Laughing]
-Whoo-hoo-hoo!

56:38.150 --> 56:40.485
-[Crowd Cheering]
-[Both] Olé!

56:46.241 --> 56:48.410
-[Crowd Chanting, Indistinct]
-[All] Huh?

56:48.535 --> 56:51.038
-[Women Cheering]
-Hmm.

56:52.205 --> 56:53.582
Yes! [Laughs]

56:53.665 --> 56:55.584
-Who's the god?
-You de god.

56:55.667 --> 56:58.795
-No, you the god. Fine.
-No, you de god.

56:58.920 --> 57:03.467
[Giggling]
Y-Yeah! Yeah!

57:03.550 --> 57:06.470
[Coughs]

57:11.266 --> 57:14.311
Guys, it's here!
It's right here with me!

57:14.394 --> 57:17.939
-[Both Gasp]
-[Altivo Whinnies]

57:25.280 --> 57:28.450
[Gasping]

57:28.492 --> 57:30.285
-[All Gasping]
-[Chittering]

57:35.457 --> 57:37.501
Mmm.

57:39.336 --> 57:42.130
[Cheering]

57:45.008 --> 57:48.303
-[Horn Sounding]
-I love this game! [Laughing]

57:48.387 --> 57:50.347
-[Both] Yes!
-[Laughing]

57:50.430 --> 57:53.183
-[Laughing]
-Well done, partner.

57:53.308 --> 57:56.853
-Yes! Yes!
-My lords,
congratulations on your victory.

57:56.979 --> 58:00.023
And now, you will, of course,
wish to have the losing team...

58:00.148 --> 58:02.609
-sacrificed to your glory.
-[Crowd Gasping]

58:02.693 --> 58:04.695
[Groaning]

58:04.778 --> 58:06.822
Not again.

58:06.905 --> 58:08.949
-Look, Tzekel-Kan,
-Uh, Miguel?

58:09.074 --> 58:11.410
-forget the sacrifices.
-Miguel.

58:11.535 --> 58:14.246
We don't want any sacrifices.

58:14.329 --> 58:19.084
But all of the sacred writings
say that you will devour
the wicked and the unrighteous.

58:19.209 --> 58:22.004
Well, I don't see anyone here
who fits that description.

58:22.129 --> 58:25.465
[Scoffs]
Well, as speaker for the gods,

58:25.591 --> 58:29.845
it would be my privilege
to point them out.

58:29.928 --> 58:32.806
The gods are speaking
for themselves now!

58:32.889 --> 58:35.225
This city and these people...

58:35.309 --> 58:37.436
have no need for you anymore!

58:37.519 --> 58:39.813
[Grunts]

58:39.897 --> 58:42.482
There will be no sacrifices!

58:42.608 --> 58:46.069
-Not now, not ever!
-[Crowd Cheering]

58:47.321 --> 58:50.824
-Get out!
-[Gasps]

58:52.576 --> 58:56.371
-[Scoffs]
-[Cheering Continues]

58:56.496 --> 58:58.540
[Gasps]

58:58.624 --> 59:01.209
[Low Growl]

59:01.335 --> 59:05.589
Mmm. As the...

59:05.672 --> 59:09.426
gods... command.

59:09.509 --> 59:11.053
-[Laughing]
-[Crowd Cheering]

59:11.178 --> 59:13.513
Whoa! Who-o-oa!

59:13.639 --> 59:17.184
Hey, not bad for
my first commandment, huh? [Laughs]

59:17.309 --> 59:19.728
Miguel, the little voice--
[Stammers]

59:19.770 --> 59:21.730
Yeah, fine.

59:25.108 --> 59:28.612
Do you know why
the gods demand blood?

59:28.737 --> 59:31.865
-I don't know.
-[Grunts]

59:31.990 --> 59:34.868
Because gods don't bleed.

59:38.455 --> 59:42.000
It's time to take the future
into my own hands,

59:42.084 --> 59:44.503
and this city will be cleansed.

59:44.628 --> 59:47.256
Even if I have to do it myself.

59:47.339 --> 59:49.675
-Uh, how?
-[Grunts]

59:49.758 --> 59:53.470
There are dark magics here...

59:53.554 --> 59:56.139
and power... and--

59:56.265 --> 59:59.184
Ooh. My, my, my, my, my.

59:59.268 --> 01:00:02.604
It's not called
the Age of the Jaguar for nothing.

01:00:02.729 --> 01:00:06.775
[Snickering]

01:00:06.859 --> 01:00:12.114
This'll be a delightful way
to bid the false gods... good-bye.

01:00:15.409 --> 01:00:18.328
[Workers Shouting]

01:00:24.710 --> 01:00:26.587
Hmm.

01:00:26.712 --> 01:00:29.131
-Adios, muchacho!
-[Chuckles]

01:00:32.926 --> 01:00:36.263
-[Chuckles, Gasps]
-[Birds Chirping]

01:00:38.515 --> 01:00:40.434
[Pleasurable Moan]

01:00:40.517 --> 01:00:43.478
[Workers Shouting]

01:00:44.938 --> 01:00:48.358
-Well, it's, um, uh, nice.
-Nice?

01:00:48.483 --> 01:00:50.194
-Yes, nice.
-But?

01:00:50.319 --> 01:00:54.490
Um, but, uh,
is it really fit for the gods?

01:00:54.573 --> 01:00:56.492
-My lord.
-[Chuckles]

01:00:56.575 --> 01:01:00.537
I have been around boats, believe me,

01:01:00.662 --> 01:01:04.249
and that, um--
the pointy, tall, um--

01:01:04.333 --> 01:01:06.335
the-the-the-the long
up and down thing--

01:01:06.460 --> 01:01:09.588
-The mast?
-The mast, yes, yes. The mast is good.

01:01:09.713 --> 01:01:13.383
Well, look at it. [Stammering]
There's not nearly enough, uh,

01:01:13.509 --> 01:01:15.427
um, rope.

01:01:15.511 --> 01:01:18.722
-Rope?
-Yes, rope. Exactly my point.

01:01:18.847 --> 01:01:22.601
Vertical ascension requires
a lot more, uh, rope.

01:01:22.684 --> 01:01:26.855
-My lord. [Chuckles]
-And look at this. [Grunting]

01:01:26.939 --> 01:01:30.234
[Sighs, Clears Throat]
This doesn't look at all secure.

01:01:30.359 --> 01:01:35.531
Chief, I'm sorry. I'm sorry, but all
in all, it is a complete do-over.

01:01:39.576 --> 01:01:41.495
Hmm.

01:01:43.580 --> 01:01:45.958
You know, Lord Miguel,

01:01:46.041 --> 01:01:48.460
if you wish to stay,

01:01:48.585 --> 01:01:50.879
you only need to say so.

01:01:52.005 --> 01:01:55.968
-You mean... forever?
-Of course.

01:02:00.055 --> 01:02:02.975
Oh, no, I can't.
I have to go back with Tulio.

01:02:03.100 --> 01:02:05.102
We're-We're partners.

01:02:06.478 --> 01:02:08.897
Big plans in the other world, huh?

01:02:10.357 --> 01:02:12.568
Yep. Big plans.

01:02:12.651 --> 01:02:17.197
Well, then,
I better go get some more rope, huh?

01:02:17.322 --> 01:02:20.117
Oh, Chief, um,
forget about the rope.

01:02:20.242 --> 01:02:22.202
Um, my mistake.

01:02:22.327 --> 01:02:25.456
Hey, to err is human.

01:02:38.427 --> 01:02:40.345
-[Tulio]Half?.
-Mm-hmm.

01:02:42.097 --> 01:02:44.808
[Laughing]
I don't think so.

01:02:44.892 --> 01:02:48.562
I-I'll tell you what. Uh, I'll let you
come back to Spain with us,

01:02:48.645 --> 01:02:52.858
like you wanted, and, um, yeah,
I can see my way clear to throwing you,

01:02:52.983 --> 01:02:54.943
mmm, ten percent?

01:02:55.027 --> 01:02:59.198
[Chuckles] You know, maybe I won't go
to Spain with you and take a third.

01:02:59.281 --> 01:03:01.450
Ohh! [Chuckling]

01:03:01.575 --> 01:03:03.827
Like you don't wanna go to Spain.

01:03:03.911 --> 01:03:06.789
Oh, like you don't want me
to want to go to Spain.

01:03:06.914 --> 01:03:11.418
-I want you to want... what you want.
-Mm-hmm?

01:03:11.543 --> 01:03:13.712
Mm-hmm. Go on.

01:03:13.796 --> 01:03:17.216
All right.
Cards on the table.

01:03:17.341 --> 01:03:21.345
Uh, I want you to come to Spain
with me and Miguel.

01:03:21.470 --> 01:03:23.806
Mostly me.
Especially me.

01:03:23.889 --> 01:03:25.849
Only me.
Forget Miguel.

01:03:25.891 --> 01:03:31.563
[Chuckles] Well, as long as
that's what you want.

01:03:31.688 --> 01:03:34.441
-Me too.
-Okay.

01:03:34.566 --> 01:03:36.860
Deal?

01:03:36.944 --> 01:03:40.030
-Deal. Mmm.
-[Plate Clattering]

01:03:40.114 --> 01:03:43.409
[Hoof beats]

01:03:43.492 --> 01:03:45.702
[Gasps]

01:03:45.828 --> 01:03:47.746
"Forget Miguel"?
[Sniffling]

01:03:47.830 --> 01:03:50.457
Well, forget Tulio.

01:03:55.504 --> 01:03:58.841
[Nickering]

01:04:04.054 --> 01:04:05.973
[Humming]

01:04:07.474 --> 01:04:10.269
Well, is it ready yet?

01:04:16.024 --> 01:04:17.901
Ooh.

01:04:19.570 --> 01:04:22.197
Ah! [Sniffing]

01:04:22.322 --> 01:04:24.908
Ahh! Hmm.

01:04:24.992 --> 01:04:29.455
-It seems to be missing something.
-[Humming]

01:04:29.580 --> 01:04:31.665
Ah, that's it.

01:04:32.791 --> 01:04:36.962
-It needs more... body.
-[Grunts]

01:04:40.632 --> 01:04:42.468
[Gasping]

01:04:42.551 --> 01:04:45.262
[Hysterical Laughter]

01:04:58.192 --> 01:04:59.610
[Grunts]

01:05:00.819 --> 01:05:02.780
[Grunts]

01:05:02.905 --> 01:05:04.573
[Grunting]

01:05:08.660 --> 01:05:13.248
-[Growling]
-Do... as I command!

01:05:15.459 --> 01:05:18.128
-[Tzekel-Kan Laughing]
-[Jaguar Laughing]

01:05:18.587 --> 01:05:20.756
-The gods deserve a proper tribute.
-[Chittering]

01:05:20.881 --> 01:05:24.218
-Stop! There will be no sacrifices!
-[Laughing]

01:05:24.343 --> 01:05:28.263
[Chuckling]
That kid does you better than you do.

01:05:28.347 --> 01:05:30.808
[Sighs]
Some send-off, huh?

01:05:30.891 --> 01:05:34.895
We're finally at the "go back to Spain
and live like kings" part.

01:05:34.978 --> 01:05:38.399
[Children Laughing]

01:05:38.524 --> 01:05:40.442
[Nickers]

01:05:40.526 --> 01:05:42.695
Ooh-hoo-hoo.

01:05:42.820 --> 01:05:48.450
Well, isn't king
kind of a step down from god?

01:05:48.492 --> 01:05:50.786
What? Wh-Whoa, whoa, whoa.

01:05:50.911 --> 01:05:53.831
Miguel, we can't stay here.
[Chuckling]

01:05:53.914 --> 01:05:56.000
We have a plan, remember?

01:05:56.125 --> 01:06:01.714
How about... we forget the plan?
Hmm?

01:06:01.797 --> 01:06:04.300
-What?
-[Jaguar Roaring]

01:06:04.425 --> 01:06:07.303
[Roaring Continues]

01:06:07.386 --> 01:06:09.847
[Both Screaming]

01:06:09.930 --> 01:06:11.849
[Evil Laughter]

01:06:11.932 --> 01:06:16.812
Now everyone will know
the truth of your divinity.

01:06:22.943 --> 01:06:24.820
[Shouts]

01:06:24.903 --> 01:06:26.530
[Screams]

01:06:29.908 --> 01:06:32.119
[Screaming Continues]

01:06:34.538 --> 01:06:36.457
I'm okay!

01:06:36.582 --> 01:06:38.792
I'm still okay!

01:06:38.917 --> 01:06:41.629
Come on! Get on!

01:06:43.464 --> 01:06:45.424
[Whinnying]

01:06:45.507 --> 01:06:47.843
-[Chel Screams]
-[Tulio, Miguel Shout]

01:06:47.926 --> 01:06:49.511
[Tulio] Altivo, hyah!

01:06:53.265 --> 01:06:54.850
-[Whinnies]
-Whoa!

01:06:56.435 --> 01:06:58.771
-[Tulio Shouts]
-[Nickers]

01:06:58.854 --> 01:07:01.148
-[Groans]
-[Whinnies]

01:07:01.273 --> 01:07:03.734
-[Grunts]
-[Both Grunt]

01:07:06.528 --> 01:07:08.364
Tulio!

01:07:08.489 --> 01:07:12.826
Hey, over here,
you big Tzekel-Kan cat creep!

01:07:12.952 --> 01:07:15.913
-[Growls]
-Altivo, get Chel out of here.

01:07:15.996 --> 01:07:19.041
[Whinnying]

01:07:19.166 --> 01:07:22.127
-[Roars]
-[Both Yelling]

01:07:28.884 --> 01:07:30.761
Duck!

01:07:30.886 --> 01:07:34.056
[Roaring]

01:07:34.139 --> 01:07:36.850
[Panting, Yelling]

01:07:39.561 --> 01:07:41.563
Who-o-o-oa!

01:07:41.689 --> 01:07:45.109
[Both Gasping, Yelling]

01:07:48.404 --> 01:07:50.155
Move! Move!

01:07:52.908 --> 01:07:55.619
-Jump!
-[Roaring]

01:07:58.372 --> 01:08:00.791
[Both Yelling]

01:08:09.091 --> 01:08:11.385
[Both]
Who-o-o-a!

01:08:13.262 --> 01:08:15.306
I know what you are,

01:08:16.974 --> 01:08:19.350
and I know what you are not!

01:08:19.475 --> 01:08:22.813
And you are not gods!

01:08:25.524 --> 01:08:27.984
Y-You're not a god?

01:08:28.109 --> 01:08:29.944
You lied to me?

01:08:30.069 --> 01:08:31.988
[Clears Throat]

01:08:34.283 --> 01:08:37.828
-How dare you!
-Hey, it was his stupid plan!

01:08:37.912 --> 01:08:42.875
-What?
-Oh, oh, oh.
My plan was that we should lie low!

01:08:42.957 --> 01:08:48.296
But your plan was to run off and be all
"Oh, look at me. Look at me. I'm a god."

01:08:48.380 --> 01:08:51.050
-That's not true!
-No? Who are you kidding?

01:08:51.133 --> 01:08:53.093
You're buying your own con!

01:08:53.176 --> 01:08:55.136
At least I'm not dating mine.

01:08:55.220 --> 01:08:58.765
I-Ooh, low blow.

01:08:58.890 --> 01:09:02.770
Listen, Mr. High and Mighty,
we'd both be sailing out of here
with a mountain of gold...

01:09:02.853 --> 01:09:04.979
-if you had just listened to me!
-[Grunts]

01:09:05.104 --> 01:09:10.236
Well, now you've got all
the precious gold and Chel.
So what do you need me for?

01:09:10.319 --> 01:09:13.072
Well, maybe I don't need you anymore.

01:09:13.154 --> 01:09:16.325
Well, then, why don't you just go back
to Spain, and I'll stay here,

01:09:16.450 --> 01:09:18.327
and we'll both get what we want!

01:09:18.410 --> 01:09:21.538
-That's... fine with me, pal!
-Fine with me too!
-Ooh.

01:09:21.663 --> 01:09:23.457
-Fine!
-Ouch.
-Okay!

01:09:23.582 --> 01:09:27.002
-[Evil Chuckling]
-[Both] All right!

01:09:27.127 --> 01:09:29.046
Tie him up!

01:09:29.171 --> 01:09:31.381
-[Roaring]
-What?

01:09:31.465 --> 01:09:33.216
-[Jaguar Roaring]
-Whoa.

01:09:33.341 --> 01:09:35.594
-[Roaring Continues]
-[Both Gasp]
-Jump!

01:09:35.678 --> 01:09:37.680
[Both] Whoa!

01:09:37.763 --> 01:09:40.057
[Gasps]

01:09:42.017 --> 01:09:45.020
[Both Yelling]

01:09:45.104 --> 01:09:50.901
No-o-o-o-o!

01:10:05.958 --> 01:10:08.836
[Gasping, Panting]

01:10:10.880 --> 01:10:12.798
-[Sword Clangs]
-[Gasps]

01:10:14.091 --> 01:10:16.260
-[Gasps]
-[Whinnies]

01:10:16.385 --> 01:10:18.888
[Shuddering]

01:10:18.971 --> 01:10:20.890
My lord.

01:10:27.688 --> 01:10:29.690
Where did you get this?

01:10:33.486 --> 01:10:37.740
[Chuckling]
That was good, huh?

01:10:41.035 --> 01:10:43.829
[Grunting]

01:10:47.917 --> 01:10:50.085
[Cheering]

01:10:57.551 --> 01:11:00.721
-[Cheering Continues]
-Hey, a little help, please?

01:11:00.846 --> 01:11:04.141
Chief Tanni! Chief Tanni!

01:11:05.810 --> 01:11:09.772
-I've decided to stay.
-Oh, this is wonderful news.

01:11:09.897 --> 01:11:12.650
What a glorious day for El Dorado.

01:11:12.775 --> 01:11:16.737
Lord Miguel has decided
to live among us!

01:11:16.862 --> 01:11:19.281
Tulio!

01:11:19.365 --> 01:11:22.451
-Is everything okay?
-[Cheering Continues]

01:11:26.705 --> 01:11:30.126
Everything is... fine.

01:11:36.340 --> 01:11:39.260
[Wind Howling]

01:11:52.398 --> 01:11:54.275
There isn't much

01:11:54.400 --> 01:11:56.485
I haven't shared

01:11:57.736 --> 01:12:01.824
With you along the road

01:12:01.907 --> 01:12:06.370
And through it all
there'll always be

01:12:06.454 --> 01:12:09.540
Tomorrow's episode

01:12:10.666 --> 01:12:14.587
Suddenly that isn't true

01:12:14.670 --> 01:12:19.383
There's another avenue

01:12:19.508 --> 01:12:23.179
-Beckoning the great divide
-[Grunts]

01:12:23.304 --> 01:12:25.806
Ask no questions

01:12:25.890 --> 01:12:28.350
Take no side

01:12:28.476 --> 01:12:32.521
Who's to say who's right or wrong

01:12:32.646 --> 01:12:35.900
Whose course is braver run

01:12:36.984 --> 01:12:40.654
All I know is all we had

01:12:40.738 --> 01:12:44.158
Is over

01:12:44.283 --> 01:12:46.202
Said and done

01:12:50.456 --> 01:12:55.002
Friends never say good-bye

01:12:58.130 --> 01:13:00.091
[Chorus]Friends

01:13:00.132 --> 01:13:04.595
Never say good-bye

01:13:04.720 --> 01:13:06.806
[Chattering]

01:13:06.931 --> 01:13:08.641
Ha!

01:13:08.724 --> 01:13:11.227
[Villagers Laughing]

01:13:19.193 --> 01:13:21.862
Ahhh! Whew!

01:13:33.332 --> 01:13:37.795
-Mmm.
-Friends never say good-bye

01:13:37.920 --> 01:13:41.799
-[Children Giggling]
-[Man] Take care.

01:13:41.924 --> 01:13:43.801
-[Child] We'll miss you!
-Thank you.

01:13:43.926 --> 01:13:47.555
-Never say good-bye
-[Nickers]

01:13:47.680 --> 01:13:49.557
[Groans]

01:13:51.058 --> 01:13:53.769
-[Groans]
-[Chuckles]

01:14:07.199 --> 01:14:11.287
-[Giggling]
-Friends never say

01:14:11.370 --> 01:14:13.497
Good-bye

01:14:16.042 --> 01:14:17.585
[Chorus]Friends

01:14:17.710 --> 01:14:22.298
Never say good-bye

01:14:24.258 --> 01:14:26.635
Well, good luck.

01:14:27.803 --> 01:14:30.181
Yeah. You too.

01:14:32.767 --> 01:14:35.353
Never

01:14:35.436 --> 01:14:39.148
Say good-bye

01:14:41.233 --> 01:14:43.110
[Nickering]

01:14:45.112 --> 01:14:47.406
[Nickering Continues]

01:14:50.618 --> 01:14:52.662
-[Villagers Gasping]
-Whoa.

01:14:52.745 --> 01:14:55.748
-Whoa, boy, what is it?
-[Loud Nickering]

01:14:55.873 --> 01:14:58.209
[Man Shouting]

01:14:58.292 --> 01:15:01.504
-[Explosions]
-[Chattering]

01:15:01.587 --> 01:15:04.924
-Cortes.
-My lord, what is it?

01:15:05.049 --> 01:15:08.844
Chief Tanni!
Chief Tanni!

01:15:08.969 --> 01:15:12.765
-Approaching the city...
is an army of strangers.
-[Weapons Firing]

01:15:12.890 --> 01:15:17.269
We are safe here.
They'll never find the gate to the city.

01:15:17.353 --> 01:15:21.565
But, sire, they are being led
by Tzekel-Kan.

01:15:21.691 --> 01:15:25.736
He survived!
Warriors, prepare yourselves for battle!

01:15:25.861 --> 01:15:28.072
[All Shouting]

01:15:28.155 --> 01:15:30.116
Chief, you cannot fight them!

01:15:30.199 --> 01:15:32.368
Then how can we stop them?

01:15:32.451 --> 01:15:34.370
We can't.

01:15:40.960 --> 01:15:43.212
-Hmm.
-[Firing Continues]

01:15:44.338 --> 01:15:46.549
Uh, one moment, please.

01:15:49.885 --> 01:15:52.972
-Okay, here's the gate. Here's the boat.
-Uh-huh. And?

01:15:53.097 --> 01:15:55.057
-Here's the gate. Here's the boat.
-Okay.

01:15:55.141 --> 01:15:58.602
-Got that. And? Tulio!
-Well, here's the "goat,"
and here's the "bate."

01:15:58.728 --> 01:16:00.187
[Shouts]

01:16:01.981 --> 01:16:05.735
-[Chittering]
-[Gasps] That's it.

01:16:05.860 --> 01:16:07.903
We'll crash the boat
into the pillars.

01:16:07.987 --> 01:16:11.490
That's it? I mean--
But-[Scoffs]

01:16:11.616 --> 01:16:14.577
-What about the gold?
-Well-[Sobbing]

01:16:15.953 --> 01:16:18.247
[Whiny Voice] Chief!.
[Clears Throat]

01:16:18.331 --> 01:16:20.291
[Normal Voice] Chief.

01:16:20.374 --> 01:16:22.251
I've got a plan.

01:16:28.341 --> 01:16:31.260
[Villagers Shouting]

01:16:32.887 --> 01:16:36.557
Hold the line steady!
They're almost in place!

01:16:36.682 --> 01:16:38.726
[Whinnying]

01:16:40.519 --> 01:16:44.440
It better be there, for your sake.

01:16:57.703 --> 01:16:59.580
[Sighs]

01:17:02.291 --> 01:17:06.170
Okay, Chief, on my signal!

01:17:07.797 --> 01:17:10.675
Ready! Hit the pillars!

01:17:10.800 --> 01:17:13.761
-Now!
-[Shouting Continues]

01:17:17.974 --> 01:17:19.892
-[Rumbling]
-[Gasps]

01:17:20.017 --> 01:17:23.938
[Weapons Firing]

01:17:25.481 --> 01:17:27.483
-They're breaking too fast!
-Tulio, the sail!

01:17:27.608 --> 01:17:29.485
[Grunting]

01:17:30.987 --> 01:17:33.281
[Grunting Continues]
It's stuck!

01:17:35.324 --> 01:17:37.451
[All Grunting]

01:17:37.535 --> 01:17:39.495
-[Both Shout]
-[Gasps]

01:17:43.165 --> 01:17:45.543
They're not gonna make it. Altivo!

01:17:46.502 --> 01:17:49.547
[Nickering]

01:17:49.630 --> 01:17:51.549
-[Whinnying]
-[Shouts]

01:17:56.846 --> 01:17:58.764
-[Whinnies]
-Are you crazy?

01:18:11.944 --> 01:18:14.030
[Yelling]

01:18:15.698 --> 01:18:18.409
Get off the boat, Miguel,
or you'll never see the city again.

01:18:18.492 --> 01:18:22.496
I know. You don't think I'm gonna
let you have all the fun, do you?

01:18:22.580 --> 01:18:26.042
Come on.
We've got a wave to catch.

01:18:36.385 --> 01:18:38.554
-[Yelling]
-[Whimpers]

01:18:49.690 --> 01:18:52.610
-Get out of the way!
-Huh?

01:18:54.195 --> 01:18:56.239
Hold on!

01:19:02.995 --> 01:19:04.997
-Whoa!
-[Whinnies]

01:19:13.214 --> 01:19:16.425
We're gonna have to hit it broadside!

01:19:16.509 --> 01:19:19.720
That's your plan?
But the gold!

01:19:19.846 --> 01:19:22.098
-I know!
-[Gasps]

01:19:22.181 --> 01:19:25.101
Just turn the boat!

01:19:25.184 --> 01:19:28.771
On impact, everybody jump!

01:19:38.239 --> 01:19:40.241
[Gasping, Groaning]

01:19:56.757 --> 01:19:59.260
[Coughing]

